{"schemaVersion":1,"eventId":"evt-2abb1a8a-bb2d-436b-9b1e-9ad9c26bb73e","sequence":2325,"parentEventId":"evt-5cfbd2b5-7db5-4e3a-a833-04dd156141d6","recordedAt":"2026-07-01T02:58:09.577Z","actor":{"id":"unknown","source":"system"},"command":{"name":"create-task","moduleId":"task-engine"},"kind":"task.updated","payload":{"taskId":"T100776","changedFields":["priority","approach","technicalScope","acceptanceCriteria","metadata"],"values":{"priority":"P2","approach":"Echo the authoritative current phase (workspaceStatus.currentKitPhase / phaseResolution.canonicalPhaseKey) in get-next-actions output and in the start-idea-planning planner bootstrap context, and default planner phaseRecommendations / finalize target phase from that resolved value instead of per-task phaseKey tags.","technicalScope":["src/modules/task-engine (get-next-actions projection: add resolved currentKitPhase / canonicalPhaseKey to response envelope)","src/modules/ideas (start-idea-planning bootstrap: include canonical current phase in returned planning context)","src/modules/planning (default phaseRecommendations / finalize-plan-to-phase target from workspaceStatus.currentKitPhase when unset)"],"acceptanceCriteria":["get-next-actions response includes the resolved canonical current phase (e.g. currentKitPhase) at the envelope/data level, distinct from per-task phaseKey tags","start-idea-planning returns the canonical current phase in its planning context so planner-chat does not infer phase from task tags","Planner phase defaults (phaseRecommendations primary and finalize target) resolve from workspaceStatus.currentKitPhase when not explicitly provided","Unit/integration tests assert the resolved current phase is correct even when the ready queue contains tasks tagged with an older phaseKey"],"metadata":{"issue":"Agents can mis-detect the current phase because get-next-actions (and the planner bootstrap) only expose per-task phaseKey tags, not the authoritative workspace phase. When the ready queue lags a phase rollover, an agent inferring 'current phase' from those tags picks the wrong phase.","supportingReasoning":"Observed live during planner-chat for idea I004 (session pcs-b75f9d29): get-next-actions returned a ready queue uniformly tagged phaseKey 109, and the agent inferred current phase = 109. The operator corrected it to 140. dashboard-summary.data.workspaceStatus.currentKitPhase and the phaseResolution block ('Current phase 140 (workspace-status)') both correctly reported 140, but that authoritative field is absent from get-next-actions output, so the agent anchored on the lagging per-task tag. Evidence: dashboard-summary.workspaceStatus.currentKitPhase=140 vs ready-queue task phaseKey=109.","sourceIdeaId":"I004","planningSessionRef":"pcs-b75f9d29-59f0-4c7f-b453-75cc083aad33"}}},"expectedTaskVersion":1}
