{"schemaVersion":1,"eventId":"evt-82cd5b2b-8bcd-4a69-a786-0bd32ec92e11","sequence":2351,"parentEventId":"evt-d95c260e-6965-4a23-a064-9575ad095671","recordedAt":"2026-07-02T06:03:57.473Z","actor":{"id":"NJLaPrell@gmail.com","source":"system"},"command":{"name":"persist-planning-execution-drafts","moduleId":"task-engine"},"kind":"task.updated","payload":{"taskId":"T100777","changedFields":["summary","description","approach","technicalScope","acceptanceCriteria","phase","phaseKey","metadata"],"values":{"summary":"Document storage model decision in ADR (file-based artifact pattern; no new SQLite column). Author TypeScript enum and types for six-state machine, IdeaPlanDocument envelope, AgentDirective, and BrainstormSession.","description":"Plan WBS row: WBS-1A (1.1) — Storage model decision and six-state machine TypeScript types\n\nApproach:\nDocument the storage model decision in an ADR: the unified IdeaPlan document uses the existing plan-artifact file convention (.workspace-kit/planning/plan-artifacts/<uuid>/artifact.vN.json); the SQLite ideas row's linked_plan_artifact column references the file; no new SQLite column is needed. Author TypeScript enum and type definitions for the six-state machine (IdeaPlanStatus, IdeaPlanDocument envelope, AgentDirective shape, BrainstormSession record shape). No schema files yet — types only.\n\nGoal mapping:\n- A single document traces an idea from inception through brainstorming, planning, review, acceptance, and delivery — no separate entities to keep in sync\n- The document status advances through six states: idea → brainstorming → planning → reviewed → accepted → delivered\n- Each state has a machine-readable schema file with an agentDirective section that prescribes required agent behavior for that state — agents read the state schema and follow it, not playbook prose\n- US-5\n\nTechnical scope:\n- src/modules/ideas/ (TypeScript types: IdeaPlanStatus enum, IdeaPlanDocument envelope type, AgentDirective type, BrainstormSession type)\n- ADR or inline decision record for storage model choice\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- IdeaPlanStatus enum defines all six states with valid transition table\n- IdeaPlanDocument TypeScript type compiles with all progressive sections typed as optional beyond the envelope\n- AgentDirective and BrainstormSession types compile clean\n- Storage model decision (file-based artifact pattern, linked_plan_artifact references the file) documented in an ADR with rationale\n\nVerification:\n- TypeScript compiler passes with zero errors on all new type definitions\n- Unit test: IdeaPlanStatus transition table rejects invalid state transitions\n\nDone means:\nTypeScript types for the unified document and six-state machine are committed and compile clean; storage model ADR committed documenting the file-based pattern\n\nRisk notes:\nStorage model is resolved (file-based artifact pattern, D6); the remaining risk is TypeScript type correctness for the progressive sections — compile clean before proceeding to WBS-1B","approach":"Document storage model decision in ADR (file-based artifact pattern; no new SQLite column). Author TypeScript enum and types for six-state machine, IdeaPlanDocument envelope, AgentDirective, and BrainstormSession.","technicalScope":["src/modules/ideas/ (TypeScript types)","ADR for storage model decision"],"acceptanceCriteria":["IdeaPlanStatus enum with valid transition table","IdeaPlanDocument, AgentDirective, BrainstormSession types compile clean","Storage model decision (file-based artifact pattern) documented in ADR with rationale"],"phase":"Phase 140","phaseKey":"140","metadata":{"planRef":"plan-artifact:f7a3b891-c5d2-4e6f-9a08-1b2c3d4e5f60","planningProvenance":{"planId":"f7a3b891-c5d2-4e6f-9a08-1b2c3d4e5f60","planVersion":19,"wbsId":"WBS-1A","wbsPath":"1.1","planRef":"plan-artifact:f7a3b891-c5d2-4e6f-9a08-1b2c3d4e5f60","planningType":"new-feature","sourceIdeaId":"I005","source":"persist-planning-execution-drafts"}}}},"workspace":{"phaseKey":"140"},"expectedTaskVersion":1}
