{"schemaVersion":1,"eventId":"evt-3b82d131-0b85-4af9-aba5-50c73d3a1e7c","sequence":2353,"parentEventId":"evt-c1edfb88-9758-428b-b61c-7246d3388391","recordedAt":"2026-07-02T06:03:57.473Z","actor":{"id":"NJLaPrell@gmail.com","source":"system"},"command":{"name":"persist-planning-execution-drafts","moduleId":"task-engine"},"kind":"task.updated","payload":{"taskId":"T100778","changedFields":["summary","description","approach","dependsOn","technicalScope","acceptanceCriteria","phase","phaseKey","metadata"],"values":{"summary":"Author brainstorming state schema with required/optional fields, valid transitions, and complete agentDirective covering all 13 scoring sub-inputs, five score formulas verbatim, and synthesis formula. Produce session fixture. Walkthrough-test directive with a real agent.","description":"Plan WBS row: WBS-1B (1.2) — Author brainstorming state schema with full agentDirective and walkthrough test\n\nApproach:\nAuthor schemas/ideas/states/brainstorming.schema.json. Required/optional fields section: define brainstorm section as required, plan section as absent. Valid transitions: brainstorming→planning. agentDirective section: define ordered question phases (context, value-scoring, risk-scoring, effort-scoring, confidence-scoring, unknowns, alternatives, session-notes), each question with fieldName, prompt, type (score-1-10/text/enum), validRange, and guidance. Note in effort-scoring guidance that T-shirt size and complexity sub-inputs are weighted independently — a high-complexity M item intentionally scores higher than a low-complexity L. Include compute step listing all five score formulas verbatim with weights. Include synthesis-update step with explicit N=1 edge case: if sessions.length===1, synthesized=session scores; else synthesized=latest×0.60+mean(prior)×0.40. Note that session records are mutable in place — start-brainstorm-session creates the slot, update-brainstorm-session fills it progressively. Walkthrough-test the directive with a real agent session: agent must complete all phases and produce correct computed scores from the schema alone.\n\nGoal mapping:\n- A single document traces an idea from inception through brainstorming, planning, review, acceptance, and delivery — no separate entities to keep in sync\n- Each state has a machine-readable schema file with an agentDirective section that prescribes required agent behavior for that state — agents read the state schema and follow it, not playbook prose\n- The brainstorming state schema agentDirective defines the full agent-led session: ordered question phases, scoring sub-inputs, formula application steps, and synthesis update — agents must not invent a different flow\n- Each brainstorming session computes valueScore, riskScore, effortScore, confidenceScore, and priorityScore using the canonical formulas defined in the schema\n- US-5\n\nTechnical scope:\n- schemas/ideas/states/brainstorming.schema.json (new)\n- fixtures/ideas/brainstorming-session.fixture.json (one brainstorm session record for validation)\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- brainstorming.schema.json exists with required/optional fields, valid transitions, and complete agentDirective section\n- agentDirective covers all 13 scoring sub-inputs across ordered phases with prompt, type, validRange, and guidance for each\n- All five scoring formulas and synthesis formula (including N=1 edge case) are embedded verbatim with weights in the agentDirective compute step\n- effortScore guidance explicitly notes that T-shirt size and complexity sub-inputs blend intentionally\n- Session mutability model documented in schema: slot created by start-brainstorm-session, filled progressively by update-brainstorm-session\n- A brainstorming session fixture validates against the session record schema\n- Walkthrough test passed: agent read the directive cold and produced a complete, correctly scored session record\n\nVerification:\n- Unit test: brainstorming session fixture validates against brainstorm-session schema\n- Unit test: scoring formulas in directive produce correct outputs for a set of known input values\n- Unit test: N=1 synthesis returns session scores directly; N=2 applies 60/40 weighting\n- Integration walkthrough: agent completes full session from directive alone without supplementary guidance\n\nDone means:\nbrainstorming.schema.json committed with complete agentDirective; session fixture validates; walkthrough test passed\n\nRisk notes:\nThe agentDirective authoring is the most creative and error-prone step in the schema tranche — budget time for the walkthrough test AC; this is the critical path item","approach":"Author brainstorming state schema with required/optional fields, valid transitions, and complete agentDirective covering all 13 scoring sub-inputs, five score formulas verbatim, and synthesis formula. Produce session fixture. Walkthrough-test directive with a real agent.","dependsOn":["T100777"],"technicalScope":["schemas/ideas/states/brainstorming.schema.json","fixtures/ideas/brainstorming-session.fixture.json"],"acceptanceCriteria":["agentDirective covers all 13 sub-inputs with prompts, ranges, and guidance","All five score formulas and synthesis formula embedded verbatim","Walkthrough test: agent completed full session from directive alone"],"phase":"Phase 140","phaseKey":"140","metadata":{"planRef":"plan-artifact:f7a3b891-c5d2-4e6f-9a08-1b2c3d4e5f60","planningProvenance":{"planId":"f7a3b891-c5d2-4e6f-9a08-1b2c3d4e5f60","planVersion":19,"wbsId":"WBS-1B","wbsPath":"1.2","planRef":"plan-artifact:f7a3b891-c5d2-4e6f-9a08-1b2c3d4e5f60","planningType":"new-feature","sourceIdeaId":"I005","source":"persist-planning-execution-drafts"}}}},"workspace":{"phaseKey":"140"},"expectedTaskVersion":1}
