{"schemaVersion":1,"eventId":"evt-59a936c5-99ee-46b3-883e-d48a81c27ec6","sequence":2355,"parentEventId":"evt-b2640103-10c8-48f5-9bb0-fc4c418ed2e5","recordedAt":"2026-07-02T06:03:57.473Z","actor":{"id":"NJLaPrell@gmail.com","source":"system"},"command":{"name":"persist-planning-execution-drafts","moduleId":"task-engine"},"kind":"task.updated","payload":{"taskId":"T100779","changedFields":["summary","description","approach","dependsOn","technicalScope","acceptanceCriteria","phase","phaseKey","metadata"],"values":{"summary":"Author schemas/ideas/states/ files for idea, planning, reviewed, accepted, and delivered states. Each defines required/optional fields, valid transitions, and an agentDirective appropriate for that state.","description":"Plan WBS row: WBS-1C (1.3) — Author the five remaining state schemas (idea, planning, reviewed, accepted, delivered)\n\nApproach:\nAuthor schemas/ideas/states/idea.schema.json, planning.schema.json, reviewed.schema.json, accepted.schema.json, and delivered.schema.json. Each file defines: (a) required/optional fields at that state, (b) valid transitions, (c) an agentDirective section appropriate for that state (idea: no active agent session; planning: direct agent to initialize plan section and invoke planner-chat; reviewed: direct agent to present review results; accepted: direct agent to confirm acceptance record; delivered: direct agent to attach delivery refs). Follow the pattern established in WBS-1B.\n\nGoal mapping:\n- A single document traces an idea from inception through brainstorming, planning, review, acceptance, and delivery — no separate entities to keep in sync\n- The document status advances through six states: idea → brainstorming → planning → reviewed → accepted → delivered\n- Each state has a machine-readable schema file with an agentDirective section that prescribes required agent behavior for that state — agents read the state schema and follow it, not playbook prose\n- US-5\n\nTechnical scope:\n- schemas/ideas/states/idea.schema.json (new)\n- schemas/ideas/states/planning.schema.json (new)\n- schemas/ideas/states/reviewed.schema.json (new)\n- schemas/ideas/states/accepted.schema.json (new)\n- schemas/ideas/states/delivered.schema.json (new)\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- All five schema files exist under schemas/ideas/states/ with required/optional fields and valid transitions defined\n- Each schema has an agentDirective section appropriate for its state\n- Transitions chain correctly: idea→brainstorming, brainstorming→planning, planning→reviewed, reviewed→accepted, accepted→delivered\n- No state schema references brainstorming-specific scoring formulas (those live only in brainstorming.schema.json)\n\nVerification:\n- Unit test: each state schema file parses as valid JSON\n- Unit test: transition table for all six states forms a valid DAG with no cycles\n\nDone means:\nFive state schema files committed, each with required fields, transitions, and agentDirective; transition table forms a valid DAG\n\nRisk notes:\nStraightforward once the brainstorming schema pattern (WBS-1B) is established; primarily repetitive authoring","approach":"Author schemas/ideas/states/ files for idea, planning, reviewed, accepted, and delivered states. Each defines required/optional fields, valid transitions, and an agentDirective appropriate for that state.","dependsOn":["T100777","T100778"],"technicalScope":["schemas/ideas/states/ (five new schema files)"],"acceptanceCriteria":["Five schema files with required fields, transitions, and agentDirective sections","Transitions chain correctly across all six states","Transition table forms a valid DAG"],"phase":"Phase 140","phaseKey":"140","metadata":{"planRef":"plan-artifact:f7a3b891-c5d2-4e6f-9a08-1b2c3d4e5f60","planningProvenance":{"planId":"f7a3b891-c5d2-4e6f-9a08-1b2c3d4e5f60","planVersion":19,"wbsId":"WBS-1C","wbsPath":"1.3","planRef":"plan-artifact:f7a3b891-c5d2-4e6f-9a08-1b2c3d4e5f60","planningType":"new-feature","sourceIdeaId":"I005","source":"persist-planning-execution-drafts"}}}},"workspace":{"phaseKey":"140"},"expectedTaskVersion":1}
