{"schemaVersion":1,"eventId":"evt-70ed3c4f-af16-42be-9122-810d5040ebaf","sequence":2375,"parentEventId":"evt-6f0785b9-e069-4244-b4d4-4664ad425a9d","recordedAt":"2026-07-02T06:03:57.473Z","actor":{"id":"NJLaPrell@gmail.com","source":"system"},"command":{"name":"persist-planning-execution-drafts","moduleId":"task-engine"},"kind":"task.updated","payload":{"taskId":"T100789","changedFields":["summary","description","approach","dependsOn","technicalScope","acceptanceCriteria","phase","phaseKey","metadata"],"values":{"summary":"Replace Plan button with Brainstorm + Plan buttons on idea cards. Add buildBrainstormSessionPrompt to playbook-chat-prompts.ts. Brainstorm button: start-brainstorm-session → prefillCursorChat. Plan button: start-idea-planning → prefillCursorChat (skip brainstorm). Add secondary Brainstorm on detail panels.","description":"Plan WBS row: WBS-4B (4.2) — Dashboard: Brainstorm button on idea cards and secondary brainstorm button on detail panels\n\nApproach:\nReplace the Plan button on idea-state cards with two buttons: 'Brainstorm' and 'Plan'. Brainstorm button flow: (1) dashboard calls command client to run start-brainstorm-session; (2) reads brainstormChatPrompt from response; (3) calls prefillCursorChat({ newChat: true }) with the prompt — identical to existing Plan button pattern. Plan button flow (skip brainstorming): (1) calls start-idea-planning; (2) reads planningChatPrompt; (3) calls prefillCursorChat({ newChat: true }). Add buildBrainstormSessionPrompt() to extensions/cursor-workflow-cannon/src/playbook-chat-prompts.ts: includes ideaId, title, note, sessionIndex from the command response, and instructs agent to load schemas/ideas/states/brainstorming.schema.json and follow the agentDirective. Add a secondary Brainstorm button on idea detail panels for documents in any post-brainstorming state (appends session without status change).\n\nGoal mapping:\n- Agent-led brainstorming sessions are stored as an ordered array on the document and can be triggered at any document status\n- The dashboard surfaces a Brainstorm button and a Brainstorming rollup showing synthesized scores (Value, Risk, Effort, Confidence, Priority) for ideas in brainstorming state\n- US-1\n- US-2\n\nTechnical scope:\n- extensions/cursor-workflow-cannon (idea card render: replace Plan button with Brainstorm + Plan buttons)\n- extensions/cursor-workflow-cannon (idea detail panel: add secondary Brainstorm button for post-brainstorming states)\n- extensions/cursor-workflow-cannon/src/playbook-chat-prompts.ts (add buildBrainstormSessionPrompt)\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- Idea cards display Brainstorm and Plan buttons in place of the single Plan button for idea-state documents\n- Brainstorm button calls start-brainstorm-session, reads brainstormChatPrompt from response, calls prefillCursorChat({ newChat: true })\n- Plan button calls start-idea-planning (skipping brainstorming), reads planningChatPrompt from response, calls prefillCursorChat({ newChat: true })\n- buildBrainstormSessionPrompt includes ideaId, title, note, sessionIndex, and instruction to load brainstorming state schema agentDirective\n- Idea detail panels for documents in planning, reviewed, accepted, or delivered state show a secondary Brainstorm button\n- Clicking the secondary Brainstorm button invokes start-brainstorm-session and appends a new session slot without changing document status\n\nVerification:\n- Extension unit test: Brainstorm and Plan buttons render on idea-state cards\n- Extension unit test: secondary Brainstorm button renders on detail panels for post-brainstorming states\n- Unit test: buildBrainstormSessionPrompt includes ideaId, sessionIndex, and schema load instruction\n- Integration test: Brainstorm button click invokes start-brainstorm-session then prefillCursorChat with brainstormChatPrompt\n- Integration test: Plan button click invokes start-idea-planning then prefillCursorChat with planningChatPrompt\n\nDone means:\nBrainstorm button on idea cards and secondary button on detail panels working; extension tests pass\n\nRisk notes:\nEnsure the secondary brainstorm button is gated correctly by document state to avoid showing it on idea-state documents","approach":"Replace Plan button with Brainstorm + Plan buttons on idea cards. Add buildBrainstormSessionPrompt to playbook-chat-prompts.ts. Brainstorm button: start-brainstorm-session → prefillCursorChat. Plan button: start-idea-planning → prefillCursorChat (skip brainstorm). Add secondary Brainstorm on detail panels.","dependsOn":["T100788"],"technicalScope":["extensions/cursor-workflow-cannon (idea card, detail panel)","extensions/cursor-workflow-cannon/src/playbook-chat-prompts.ts"],"acceptanceCriteria":["Brainstorm and Plan buttons on idea-state cards","buildBrainstormSessionPrompt includes ideaId, sessionIndex, schema load instruction","Button-to-agent invocation via prefillCursorChat","Secondary Brainstorm on detail panels for post-brainstorming states"],"phase":"Phase 140","phaseKey":"140","metadata":{"planRef":"plan-artifact:f7a3b891-c5d2-4e6f-9a08-1b2c3d4e5f60","planningProvenance":{"planId":"f7a3b891-c5d2-4e6f-9a08-1b2c3d4e5f60","planVersion":19,"wbsId":"WBS-4B","wbsPath":"4.2","planRef":"plan-artifact:f7a3b891-c5d2-4e6f-9a08-1b2c3d4e5f60","planningType":"new-feature","sourceIdeaId":"I005","source":"persist-planning-execution-drafts"}}}},"workspace":{"phaseKey":"140"},"expectedTaskVersion":1}
