{"schemaVersion":1,"eventId":"evt-5a98c46a-7c57-4cc6-bd45-c585f2cc4785","sequence":2379,"parentEventId":"evt-fc5cd6a7-bd43-4467-aa18-7efb7ecc560d","recordedAt":"2026-07-02T06:03:57.473Z","actor":{"id":"NJLaPrell@gmail.com","source":"system"},"command":{"name":"persist-planning-execution-drafts","moduleId":"task-engine"},"kind":"task.updated","payload":{"taskId":"T100791","changedFields":["summary","description","approach","dependsOn","technicalScope","acceptanceCriteria","phase","phaseKey","metadata"],"values":{"summary":"Author brainstorm-session.md (schema is authoritative; playbook is human companion). Update planner-chat.md, start-idea-planning.md, update-idea-planning-session.md, and PLANNER_SCHEMA.md for unified model.","description":"Plan WBS row: WBS-5 (5) — Human-companion playbooks and updated instruction files for unified document model\n\nApproach:\nAuthor brainstorm-session.md as a human-readable companion to the brainstorming state schema agentDirective — tone guidance, how to handle operator confusion, how to summarize scores after computation, effortScore sub-input relationship guidance. The schema is machine-authoritative; the playbook adds human context only and must not redefine question sequences or formulas. Update planner-chat.md for the unified document model. Update start-idea-planning.md, update-idea-planning-session.md, and PLANNER_SCHEMA.md to remove stale separate artifact references and point to per-state schema files. Document score color semantics (Value/Confidence/Priority: green-high/red-low; Risk/Effort: green-low/red-high; bands: 0–33 red, 34–66 amber, 67–100 green) and rollup sort order (priorityScore descending) as named constants in extensions/cursor-workflow-cannon/src/views/shared/ for use by WBS-4C.\n\nGoal mapping:\n- A single document traces an idea from inception through brainstorming, planning, review, acceptance, and delivery — no separate entities to keep in sync\n- Each state has a machine-readable schema file with an agentDirective section that prescribes required agent behavior for that state — agents read the state schema and follow it, not playbook prose\n- The brainstorming state schema agentDirective defines the full agent-led session: ordered question phases, scoring sub-inputs, formula application steps, and synthesis update — agents must not invent a different flow\n- US-4\n\nTechnical scope:\n- .ai/playbooks/brainstorm-session.md (new — human companion)\n- .ai/playbooks/planner-chat.md (updated for unified model)\n- src/modules/ideas/instructions/start-idea-planning.md\n- src/modules/ideas/instructions/update-idea-planning-session.md\n- PLANNER_SCHEMA.md (plan section reference update, pointer to per-state schema files)\n- extensions/cursor-workflow-cannon/src/views/shared/ (score color semantics and rollup sort constants)\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- brainstorm-session.md companion playbook exists with tone guidance and explicitly states the schema agentDirective is machine-authoritative\n- Playbook does not redefine question sequences or formulas — those live only in the schema\n- planner-chat.md references unified document model and per-state schema files\n- No instruction file references a standalone plan artifact file path\n- Score color semantics (per-score-type direction + color bands) defined as named constants importable by dashboard render code\n- Rollup sort order (priorityScore descending) documented in the constants file\n\nVerification:\n- Manual review: brainstorm-session.md does not duplicate or contradict the schema agentDirective\n- Manual review: no stale references to separate plan artifact files in any instruction file\n- Code review: score color semantic constants exist and are correctly typed for import by WBS-4C renderers\n\nDone means:\nbrainstorm-session.md companion authored; all instruction files reference unified model; no stale artifact references remain\n\nRisk notes:\nRisk is the companion playbook accidentally becoming the authoritative source — it must defer to the schema explicitly","approach":"Author brainstorm-session.md (schema is authoritative; playbook is human companion). Update planner-chat.md, start-idea-planning.md, update-idea-planning-session.md, and PLANNER_SCHEMA.md for unified model.","dependsOn":["T100778","T100787"],"technicalScope":[".ai/playbooks/brainstorm-session.md (new)",".ai/playbooks/planner-chat.md","src/modules/ideas/instructions/","PLANNER_SCHEMA.md"],"acceptanceCriteria":["Companion playbook defers to schema agentDirective as authoritative","planner-chat.md references unified model","No stale separate artifact references"],"phase":"Phase 140","phaseKey":"140","metadata":{"planRef":"plan-artifact:f7a3b891-c5d2-4e6f-9a08-1b2c3d4e5f60","planningProvenance":{"planId":"f7a3b891-c5d2-4e6f-9a08-1b2c3d4e5f60","planVersion":19,"wbsId":"WBS-5","wbsPath":"5","planRef":"plan-artifact:f7a3b891-c5d2-4e6f-9a08-1b2c3d4e5f60","planningType":"new-feature","sourceIdeaId":"I005","source":"persist-planning-execution-drafts"}}}},"workspace":{"phaseKey":"140"},"expectedTaskVersion":1}
