{"schemaVersion":1,"eventId":"evt-f0a70315-08cf-4a70-a0e6-23e7b5e49946","sequence":2385,"parentEventId":"evt-91506a38-3f48-44db-89ff-4f6df3d799c3","recordedAt":"2026-07-02T06:03:57.473Z","actor":{"id":"NJLaPrell@gmail.com","source":"system"},"command":{"name":"persist-planning-execution-drafts","moduleId":"task-engine"},"kind":"task.updated","payload":{"taskId":"T100794","changedFields":["summary","description","approach","dependsOn","technicalScope","acceptanceCriteria","phase","phaseKey","metadata"],"values":{"summary":"Update draft-plan-artifact (persist), review-plan-artifact (record-review), accept-plan-artifact, and finalize-plan-to-phase to call generate-plan-document after each successful mutation (best-effort; failure does not fail primary command).","description":"Plan WBS row: WBS-7B (7.2) — Hook generate-plan-document into planning lifecycle commands\n\nApproach:\nUpdate draft-plan-artifact (persist path), review-plan-artifact (record-review path), accept-plan-artifact, and finalize-plan-to-phase handlers to call generate-plan-document after each successful mutation. The call is best-effort: if document generation fails, log the error but do not fail the primary command. Return the generated document path in the response data as generatedPlanDocPath when generation succeeds. The plan document in docs/maintainers/plans/ is always a snapshot of the last successful mutation; it is not versioned separately.\n\nGoal mapping:\n- Every plan lifecycle event (draft persisted, reviewed, accepted, finalized) regenerates a human-readable plan document in docs/maintainers/plans/ via the documentation module infrastructure\n- US-4\n\nTechnical scope:\n- src/modules/planning/ (draft-plan-artifact handler — persist path)\n- src/modules/planning/ (review-plan-artifact handler — record-review path)\n- src/modules/planning/ (accept-plan-artifact handler)\n- src/modules/planning/ (finalize-plan-to-phase handler)\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- draft-plan-artifact persist path calls generate-plan-document and returns generatedPlanDocPath in response data on success\n- review-plan-artifact record-review path calls generate-plan-document and returns generatedPlanDocPath on success\n- accept-plan-artifact calls generate-plan-document and returns generatedPlanDocPath on success\n- finalize-plan-to-phase persist path calls generate-plan-document and returns generatedPlanDocPath on success\n- If generate-plan-document fails, the primary command still succeeds; failure is logged but not surfaced as a command error\n- docs/maintainers/plans/<ideaId>-<slug>.md reflects the state of the plan at the time of each mutation\n\nVerification:\n- Integration test: draft-plan-artifact persist returns generatedPlanDocPath and the file exists with current plan state\n- Integration test: accept-plan-artifact generates plan doc with status: accepted reflected in the rendered document\n- Unit test: generate-plan-document failure does not propagate as a primary command failure\n\nDone means:\nAll four planning lifecycle commands call generate-plan-document on persist; docs/maintainers/plans/ updated on every mutation; generatedPlanDocPath in response data\n\nRisk notes:\nBest-effort semantics for the hook are critical — do not let a doc generation failure block a plan lifecycle operation","approach":"Update draft-plan-artifact (persist), review-plan-artifact (record-review), accept-plan-artifact, and finalize-plan-to-phase to call generate-plan-document after each successful mutation (best-effort; failure does not fail primary command).","dependsOn":["T100793"],"technicalScope":["src/modules/planning/ (four command handler updates)"],"acceptanceCriteria":["All four planning commands call generate-plan-document on persist path","generatedPlanDocPath returned in response data on success","generate-plan-document failure does not fail primary command","docs/maintainers/plans/ reflects current plan state after each mutation"],"phase":"Phase 140","phaseKey":"140","metadata":{"planRef":"plan-artifact:f7a3b891-c5d2-4e6f-9a08-1b2c3d4e5f60","planningProvenance":{"planId":"f7a3b891-c5d2-4e6f-9a08-1b2c3d4e5f60","planVersion":19,"wbsId":"WBS-7B","wbsPath":"7.2","planRef":"plan-artifact:f7a3b891-c5d2-4e6f-9a08-1b2c3d4e5f60","planningType":"new-feature","sourceIdeaId":"I005","source":"persist-planning-execution-drafts"}}}},"workspace":{"phaseKey":"140"},"expectedTaskVersion":1}
{"schemaVersion":1,"eventId":"evt-af94209d-cceb-4bc5-ba83-4cb16309d714","sequence":2386,"parentEventId":"evt-f0a70315-08cf-4a70-a0e6-23e7b5e49946","recordedAt":"2026-07-02T06:03:57.473Z","actor":{"id":"NJLaPrell@gmail.com","source":"system"},"command":{"name":"persist-planning-execution-drafts","moduleId":"task-engine"},"kind":"task.created","payload":{"taskId":"T100795","initialStatus":"ready","title":"Feature flag activation gate, migration rollback runbook, and schema loader fallback","type":"workspace-kit"},"workspace":{"phaseKey":"140"}}
{"schemaVersion":1,"eventId":"evt-51aff26d-6153-4b9a-a13b-67f12e79f693","sequence":2387,"parentEventId":"evt-af94209d-cceb-4bc5-ba83-4cb16309d714","recordedAt":"2026-07-02T06:03:57.473Z","actor":{"id":"NJLaPrell@gmail.com","source":"system"},"command":{"name":"persist-planning-execution-drafts","moduleId":"task-engine"},"kind":"task.updated","payload":{"taskId":"T100795","changedFields":["summary","description","approach","dependsOn","technicalScope","acceptanceCriteria","phase","phaseKey","metadata"],"values":{"summary":"Introduce IDEAS_UNIFIED_MODEL_ENABLED feature flag (default off) gating Brainstorm button and Brainstorming rollup. Add pre-migration snapshot and rollback script for WBS-6. Implement degraded directive fallback in state-schema loader. Author rollback runbook.","description":"Plan WBS row: WBS-8 (8) — Feature flag activation gate, migration rollback runbook, and state-schema loader fallback\n\nApproach:\nFeature flag gate: introduce an IDEAS_UNIFIED_MODEL_ENABLED feature flag (default off). While the flag is off, the dashboard renders the legacy Plan button and legacy plan rollup; Brainstorm button, Brainstorming rollup, and all six-state status machine commands are unavailable. Turn the flag on only after WBS-2A through WBS-3C are deployed and the migration (WBS-6) has run. Migration rollback runbook: before the WBS-6 migration writes anything, snapshot the current SQLite ideas rows and plan artifact files to a timestamped backup directory (.workspace-kit/migration-backups/<timestamp>/). Author a rollback script that restores from the backup directory; the script dry-runs by default and requires explicit --commit to apply. Document the rollback procedure in .ai/runbooks/unified-model-rollback.md. State-schema loader fallback: if a state schema file is missing or cannot be parsed, the loader returns a degraded directive object { degraded: true, reason: <error>, requiredFields: [], validTransitions: [] } rather than throwing; callers check degraded and surface an operator-visible warning rather than crashing.\n\nGoal mapping:\n- A single document traces an idea from inception through brainstorming, planning, review, acceptance, and delivery — no separate entities to keep in sync\n- US-6\n\nTechnical scope:\n- extensions/cursor-workflow-cannon (IDEAS_UNIFIED_MODEL_ENABLED feature flag; legacy fallback for dashboard buttons and rollup)\n- src/modules/ideas/ (state-schema loader fallback — degraded directive on missing/malformed schema file)\n- .workspace-kit/migration-backups/ (snapshot target for WBS-6 migration)\n- .ai/runbooks/unified-model-rollback.md (rollback runbook)\n- scripts/ or src/modules/ideas/ (rollback script: restore from migration backup, dry-run by default)\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- IDEAS_UNIFIED_MODEL_ENABLED feature flag exists; when false, dashboard renders legacy Plan button and plan rollup; Brainstorm button and Brainstorming rollup are absent\n- When IDEAS_UNIFIED_MODEL_ENABLED is true, new buttons and rollup are rendered; legacy Plan button is replaced\n- WBS-6 migration snapshots ideas rows and plan artifact files to .workspace-kit/migration-backups/<timestamp>/ before any writes\n- Rollback script restores ideas rows and plan artifact files from the snapshot; dry-runs by default; --commit applies the restore\n- Rollback runbook at .ai/runbooks/unified-model-rollback.md documents the snapshot location, rollback script usage, and post-rollback verification steps\n- State-schema loader returns { degraded: true, reason, requiredFields: [], validTransitions: [] } when schema file is missing or malformed; does not throw\n- Callers of state-schema loader check the degraded flag and surface an operator-visible warning message rather than crashing\n\nVerification:\n- Unit test: dashboard renders legacy button when IDEAS_UNIFIED_MODEL_ENABLED is false; renders Brainstorm + Plan buttons when true\n- Unit test: state-schema loader returns degraded directive when schema file path does not exist\n- Unit test: state-schema loader returns degraded directive when schema file is not valid JSON\n- Integration test: WBS-6 migration pre-flight creates snapshot directory with expected files before any writes\n- Manual review: rollback runbook is complete and tested against a local snapshot\n\nDone means:\nFeature flag gates new UI; migration snapshot and rollback script exist and tested; state-schema loader gracefully handles missing/malformed schemas; rollback runbook committed\n\nRisk notes:\nFeature flag must be wired early enough that partial deploys (backend done, dashboard not yet) do not expose broken UI; flag defaults to off to prevent accidental exposure","approach":"Introduce IDEAS_UNIFIED_MODEL_ENABLED feature flag (default off) gating Brainstorm button and Brainstorming rollup. Add pre-migration snapshot and rollback script for WBS-6. Implement degraded directive fallback in state-schema loader. Author rollback runbook.","dependsOn":["T100781","T100789","T100792"],"technicalScope":["extensions/cursor-workflow-cannon (feature flag, legacy fallback)","src/modules/ideas/ (state-schema loader fallback)",".ai/runbooks/unified-model-rollback.md","scripts/ (rollback script)"],"acceptanceCriteria":["Feature flag gates new UI; legacy UI rendered when flag is off","Migration snapshot taken before any writes; rollback script restores from snapshot","Rollback runbook documents snapshot location, script usage, and verification","State-schema loader returns degraded directive (not throw) for missing/malformed schema"],"phase":"Phase 140","phaseKey":"140","metadata":{"planRef":"plan-artifact:f7a3b891-c5d2-4e6f-9a08-1b2c3d4e5f60","planningProvenance":{"planId":"f7a3b891-c5d2-4e6f-9a08-1b2c3d4e5f60","planVersion":19,"wbsId":"WBS-8","wbsPath":"8","planRef":"plan-artifact:f7a3b891-c5d2-4e6f-9a08-1b2c3d4e5f60","planningType":"new-feature","sourceIdeaId":"I005","source":"persist-planning-execution-drafts"}}}},"workspace":{"phaseKey":"140"},"expectedTaskVersion":1}
