{"schemaVersion":1,"eventId":"evt-2cd353f2-6691-4b19-aa73-99c48e0d9cde","sequence":2472,"parentEventId":"evt-c90ecc7b-b7c5-4078-a659-331c911e2442","recordedAt":"2026-07-03T08:48:39.459Z","actor":{"id":"NJLaPrell@gmail.com","source":"system"},"command":{"name":"create-task","moduleId":"task-engine"},"kind":"task.created","payload":{"taskId":"T100796","initialStatus":"proposed","title":"Lifecycle hooks fail open — broken enforce-mode hooks silently allow policy-gated mutations","type":"defect"}}
{"schemaVersion":1,"eventId":"evt-fe545ab5-a652-4dbf-a5f0-d5506810cb4e","sequence":2473,"parentEventId":"evt-2cd353f2-6691-4b19-aa73-99c48e0d9cde","recordedAt":"2026-07-03T08:48:39.459Z","actor":{"id":"NJLaPrell@gmail.com","source":"system"},"command":{"name":"create-task","moduleId":"task-engine"},"kind":"task.updated","payload":{"taskId":"T100796","changedFields":["summary","risk","acceptanceCriteria","metadata"],"values":{"summary":"kit-lifecycle-hooks.ts returns verdict: 'allow' whenever a hook crashes, times out, or exits with a non-zero code. Hooks configured in enforce mode to block sensitive task transitions instead let those mutations proceed silently when broken. The error is recorded in a buried response field that nothing surfaces.","risk":"high","acceptanceCriteria":["In enforce mode, a hook that exits non-zero does not silently produce verdict: 'allow'","In enforce mode, a hook that times out does not allow the mutation to proceed","In enforce mode, a spawn error results in a blocked command or prominent warning","In observe mode, existing fail-open behavior is preserved","Hook execution errors are surfaced in CLI output, not only in a buried field","New tests cover enforce-mode failure cases"],"metadata":{"issue":"Policy-gated mutations proceed even when their enforcement hooks are broken, making the hook system unreliable as a security or workflow control.","supportingReasoning":"Reviewed src/core/kit-lifecycle-hooks.ts. Both shell and Node handlers unconditionally return verdict:'allow' on exception or non-zero exit with no differentiation by hook mode. Hooks documented as capable of blocking transitions in enforce mode do not uphold this contract under failure conditions.","affectedFiles":["src/core/kit-lifecycle-hooks.ts"],"defectCategory":"correctness","discoveryMethod":"code-review"}}},"expectedTaskVersion":1}
