{"schemaVersion":1,"eventId":"evt-ba3b07ed-a884-4d6f-b441-9d8c56d44e61","sequence":2519,"parentEventId":"evt-2e82a72e-c6b6-431b-95af-aaaaff758014","recordedAt":"2026-07-07T21:27:12.540Z","actor":{"id":"workspace-kit","source":"system"},"command":{"name":"create-idea","moduleId":"ideas"},"kind":"planning.idea.created","payload":{"idea":{"id":"I009","title":"Make brainstorming a real guided ideation session that seeds the plan","note":"Current Ideas -> Brainstorm -> Plan flow models \"brainstorming\" as a scoring survey: the agentDirective is a fixed 18-question form, the brainstorm-session record only stores 13 numeric scores plus 5 fixed text fields (additionalProperties:false), and update-brainstorm-session drops anything off its allowlist. There is nowhere to store agent-generated ideas, feature suggestions, perspectives, expectations, or a conversational transcript.\n\nWorse, none of the brainstorm content seeds the plan: complete-brainstorm and buildInitialIdeaPlanPlanSection stub plan.summary from hardcoded strings, and buildIdeaPlanningPrompt never mentions the brainstorm. The synthesis only carries numeric scores forward.\n\nGoal: brainstorming should be a natural guided chat where the agent contributes ideas/perspective/feature suggestions, offers save-and-return vs finish-and-plan each turn, stores the qualitative output in the session record, and uses it to stub the first draft of the plan when promoted.\n\nCaptured via dogfood: this idea is being run through the very Ideas -> Brainstorm -> Plan pipeline it seeks to fix.","status":"open","sortOrder":8,"linkedPlanArtifact":null,"previousPlanArtifacts":[],"createdAt":"2026-07-07T21:27:12.540Z","updatedAt":"2026-07-07T21:27:12.540Z"}}}
{"schemaVersion":1,"eventId":"evt-38908a26-a819-49a0-b6a6-194a784d5e81","sequence":2520,"parentEventId":"evt-ba3b07ed-a884-4d6f-b441-9d8c56d44e61","recordedAt":"2026-07-07T21:31:50.289Z","actor":{"id":"workspace-kit","source":"system"},"command":{"name":"create-idea","moduleId":"ideas"},"kind":"planning.idea.created","payload":{"idea":{"id":"I010","title":"Agent Bug Reporting","note":"Use CAE to cause the agent to file bug report tasks when it encounters any issues related to workflow cannon or encounters agent facing features that are not easy for the agent to use.","status":"open","sortOrder":9,"linkedPlanArtifact":null,"previousPlanArtifacts":[],"createdAt":"2026-07-07T21:31:50.289Z","updatedAt":"2026-07-07T21:31:50.289Z"}}}
{"schemaVersion":1,"eventId":"evt-d7d3f821-9996-4090-8ba2-96e5811b0166","sequence":2521,"parentEventId":"evt-38908a26-a819-49a0-b6a6-194a784d5e81","recordedAt":"2026-07-07T21:36:25.220Z","actor":{"id":"workspace-kit","source":"system"},"command":{"name":"update-idea","moduleId":"ideas"},"kind":"planning.idea.updated","payload":{"idea":{"id":"I009","title":"Make brainstorming a real guided ideation session that seeds the plan","note":"# Problem\nIdeas → Brainstorm → Plan models brainstorming as a scoring survey, not guided ideation. The agentDirective is a fixed 18-question form. Session storage is additionalProperties:false with only 13 numeric scores + 5 text fields; update-brainstorm-session silently drops anything off SESSION_INPUT_FIELDS. There is no structured home for agent-generated feature ideas, perspectives, expectations, or transcript. None of the brainstorm content seeds the plan: complete-brainstorm and buildInitialIdeaPlanPlanSection use hardcoded plan.summary strings; buildIdeaPlanningPrompt never mentions brainstorm; synthesis only blends numeric scores (60/40 recency).\n\n# Goal\nA natural guided chat where the agent contributes ideas, perspective, feature suggestions, and expectations; offers save-and-return vs finish-and-plan each turn; persists qualitative output in the session record; and uses it to stub the first plan draft on promotion.\n\n# Design (target)\n1. Split session data: scoring (existing measurables) + ideation object: featureIdeas[], perspectives[], expectations[], openThreads[], decisions[], optional transcript[] ({role,text,at}).\n2. Reframe agentDirective: add agent-contribution turns (proposals/perspectives), not only elicit-from-operator questions.\n3. Per-turn checkpoint as first-class directive step (save partial session vs complete-brainstorm).\n4. Plan seed map on complete-brainstorm: featureIdeas→goals/userStories, openThreads→openQuestions, perspectives→assumptions/valueAssessment, notes→plan.summary; inject brainstorm digest into buildIdeaPlanningPrompt.\n5. Allow session completion on rich ideation even when not all 13 scores are filled (scores become optional convergent step).\n6. Create unified IdeaPlan document on create-idea (stop requiring global migrate-ideas-to-unified-document for new ideas).\n\n# Dogfood evidence (I009 session 0)\n- Agent was not guided through ideation; it bulk-filled measurables in one CLI call.\n- All qualitative content was crammed into sessionNotes because structured fields do not exist.\n- create-idea did not create a unified document; migrate-ideas-to-unified-document was required (also stamped I006/I008).\n- Migration dry-run documented as Tier C but runtime required policyApproval + expectedPlanningGeneration.\n\n# Implementation touchpoints\nschemas/ideas/brainstorm-session.schema.json, schemas/ideas/states/brainstorming.schema.json, src/modules/ideas/idea-plan-types.ts, update-brainstorm-session-handler.ts, complete-brainstorm-handler.ts, idea-plan-planning-init.ts, build-idea-planning-prompt.ts, create-idea handler (per-idea doc init), tests. Keep backward compatibility for existing sessions (I005, I007).\n\n# Scores (session 0)\nValue 7.6 | Risk 3.85 | Effort 6 | Confidence 7.3 | Priority 67 | Size M | Complexity 6\n\nUnified document: plan-artifact:08de149e-e528-4404-9e3a-885870fdf810","status":"open","sortOrder":8,"linkedPlanArtifact":"plan-artifact:08de149e-e528-4404-9e3a-885870fdf810","previousPlanArtifacts":[],"createdAt":"2026-07-07T21:27:12.540Z","updatedAt":"2026-07-07T21:36:25.219Z"}}}
