{"schemaVersion":1,"eventId":"evt-addef53f-b2c2-4fc6-8d37-10b070cfb6b7","sequence":2568,"parentEventId":"evt-b3816d64-3341-4bdf-862e-cd9efafe9ff1","recordedAt":"2026-07-08T06:16:58.212Z","actor":{"id":"NJLaPrell@gmail.com","source":"system"},"command":{"name":"update-task","moduleId":"task-engine"},"kind":"task.updated","payload":{"taskId":"T100776","changedFields":["metadata"],"values":{"metadata":{"issue":"Agents can mis-detect the current phase because get-next-actions (and the planner bootstrap) only expose per-task phaseKey tags, not the authoritative workspace phase. When the ready queue lags a phase rollover, an agent inferring 'current phase' from those tags picks the wrong phase.","supportingReasoning":"Observed live during planner-chat for idea I004 (session pcs-b75f9d29): get-next-actions returned a ready queue uniformly tagged phaseKey 109, and the agent inferred current phase = 109. The operator corrected it to 140. dashboard-summary.data.workspaceStatus.currentKitPhase and the phaseResolution block ('Current phase 140 (workspace-status)') both correctly reported 140, but that authoritative field is absent from get-next-actions output, so the agent anchored on the lagging per-task tag. Evidence: dashboard-summary.workspaceStatus.currentKitPhase=140 vs ready-queue task phaseKey=109.","sourceIdeaId":"I004","planningSessionRef":"pcs-b75f9d29-59f0-4c7f-b453-75cc083aad33","deliveryEvidence":{"schemaVersion":1,"branchName":"feature/phase-142-drain","prUrl":"https://github.com/NJLaPrell/workflow-cannon/pull/729","prNumber":729,"baseBranch":"release/phase-142","mergeSha":"1be2660dfb93c30c864fede478858db605156f41","checks":[{"name":"pre-merge-gates","conclusion":"success"}],"validationCommands":[{"command":"pnpm run pre-merge-gates","exitCode":0}]},"releaseNoteSummary":"Surface canonical current phase in get-next-actions and planner bootstrap"}}},"workspace":{"phaseKey":"142"},"expectedTaskVersion":6}
