{"schemaVersion":1,"eventId":"evt-ceef0ea2-e635-45c0-8a0a-4453de6b9ebc","sequence":2817,"parentEventId":"evt-7c211bdd-1116-4b34-b7f0-c996e89dd674","recordedAt":"2026-07-09T19:46:56.519Z","actor":{"id":"NJLaPrell@gmail.com","source":"system"},"command":{"name":"persist-planning-execution-drafts","moduleId":"task-engine"},"kind":"task.updated","payload":{"taskId":"T100843","changedFields":["priority","summary","description","approach","technicalScope","acceptanceCriteria","phase","phaseKey","metadata"],"values":{"priority":"P1","summary":"Create a single startup controller with the agreed state machine and route webview/extension startup messages through it.","description":"Plan WBS row: WBS-1 (1) — Add DashboardStartupController and route startup messages through it\n\nApproach:\nCreate a single startup controller with the agreed state machine. Inventory extension and webview entrypoints that currently trigger startup/render and redirect them to request paint, retry, or diagnostics through the controller. Ensure only one startup promise exists.\n\nGoal mapping:\n- Exactly one startup owner coordinates shell paint, bootstrap, retries, and webview boot/ready/timeout/refresh\n\nTechnical scope:\n- extensions/cursor-workflow-cannon/src\n- dashboard webview message handlers\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- DashboardStartupController owns idle → shell-painted → bootstrap-loading → hydrated → background-hydrating → ready/error\n- Inventory of webview boot/ready/timeout/refresh and extension startup entrypoints is documented; each site requests paint/retry/diagnostics through the controller only\n- Webview boot, ready, timeout, and refresh messages do not invoke a parallel full startup render\n- Only one in-flight startup promise exists for a dashboard session; concurrent requests coalesce or queue behind it\n\nVerification:\n- Unit tests for controller state transitions and single-flight startup promise\n- Tests that boot/ready/timeout/refresh request retry through the controller only\n- Regression test fails if a second full startup render starts while one is in flight\n\nDone means:\nController owns startup; inventoried call sites are routed through it; single-flight is proven by tests (mitigates R-1).\n\nRisk notes:\nR-1: Missed call sites leave residual parallel renders; inventory + single-flight gate are mandatory.","approach":"Create a single startup controller with the agreed state machine and route webview/extension startup messages through it.","technicalScope":["extensions/cursor-workflow-cannon/src","dashboard webview message handlers"],"acceptanceCriteria":["Controller owns the startup state machine","Inventoried boot/ready/timeout/refresh and extension startup sites route through the controller only","No parallel full startup renders; concurrent requests coalesce behind one in-flight promise"],"phase":"Phase 146","phaseKey":"146","metadata":{"planRef":"plan-artifact:60075304-3c0c-46c6-9c8f-468dd8ef6379","planningProvenance":{"planId":"60075304-3c0c-46c6-9c8f-468dd8ef6379","planVersion":15,"wbsId":"WBS-1","wbsPath":"1","planRef":"plan-artifact:60075304-3c0c-46c6-9c8f-468dd8ef6379","planningType":"change","sourceIdeaId":"I012","source":"persist-planning-execution-drafts"}}}},"workspace":{"phaseKey":"146"},"expectedTaskVersion":1}
