{"schemaVersion":1,"eventId":"evt-771dfa2d-3f60-4fd9-b692-76f781b71f94","sequence":2821,"parentEventId":"evt-9c85e193-b26b-4cdb-832e-d478c7572e71","recordedAt":"2026-07-09T19:46:56.519Z","actor":{"id":"NJLaPrell@gmail.com","source":"system"},"command":{"name":"persist-planning-execution-drafts","moduleId":"task-engine"},"kind":"task.updated","payload":{"taskId":"T100845","changedFields":["priority","summary","description","approach","dependsOn","technicalScope","acceptanceCriteria","phase","phaseKey","metadata"],"values":{"priority":"P1","summary":"Keep service start off critical path; prefer service when healthy; quietly promote after cold first paint.","description":"Plan WBS row: WBS-3 (3) — Background service start and quiet promote to service-primary steady-state\n\nApproach:\nStart or health-check the dashboard service off the critical path. If service is already healthy at open, prefer it for bootstrap. If it becomes healthy after cold first paint, quietly promote/patch store from service without restarting the startup pipeline or flashing the overview back to loading.\n\nGoal mapping:\n- When the service is already healthy or becomes healthy after first paint, prefer service reads without regressing the painted overview\n\nTechnical scope:\n- extensions/cursor-workflow-cannon/src\n- dashboard service startup/health handoff\n- dashboard data store\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- Service start/health is not on the critical path for first overview paint\n- Healthy-at-open path uses service without unnecessary CLI detour\n- Post-paint promote to healthy service does not clear or regress the already-usable overview\n- Promote patches/hydrates the store quietly and never restarts the startup pipeline after overview is usable\n\nVerification:\n- Test healthy-at-open prefers service\n- Test cold-then-promote patches store without restarting startup or returning to stuck loading\n- Assert promote path does not transition back through shell-painted/bootstrap-loading after hydrated\n\nDone means:\nQuiet promote never restarts startup or flashes loading after first usable overview (mitigates R-3).\n\nRisk notes:\nR-3: Promote must quiet-patch only; restarting startup after usable overview reintroduces flashes.","approach":"Keep service start off critical path; prefer service when healthy; quietly promote after cold first paint.","dependsOn":["T100843","T100844"],"technicalScope":["extensions/cursor-workflow-cannon/src","dashboard service startup/health handoff","dashboard data store"],"acceptanceCriteria":["Service start/health is off the critical path for first overview paint","Post-paint promote does not clear or regress the already-usable overview","Promote never restarts the startup pipeline after overview is usable"],"phase":"Phase 146","phaseKey":"146","metadata":{"planRef":"plan-artifact:60075304-3c0c-46c6-9c8f-468dd8ef6379","planningProvenance":{"planId":"60075304-3c0c-46c6-9c8f-468dd8ef6379","planVersion":15,"wbsId":"WBS-3","wbsPath":"3","planRef":"plan-artifact:60075304-3c0c-46c6-9c8f-468dd8ef6379","planningType":"change","sourceIdeaId":"I012","source":"persist-planning-execution-drafts"}}}},"workspace":{"phaseKey":"146"},"expectedTaskVersion":1}
