{"schemaVersion":1,"eventId":"evt-5234d0bd-b114-40ef-9590-612f03b57de7","sequence":2827,"parentEventId":"evt-1e353c73-375b-4c50-bf7d-0dbfd6e3375a","recordedAt":"2026-07-09T19:46:56.519Z","actor":{"id":"NJLaPrell@gmail.com","source":"system"},"command":{"name":"persist-planning-execution-drafts","moduleId":"task-engine"},"kind":"task.updated","payload":{"taskId":"T100848","changedFields":["priority","summary","description","approach","dependsOn","technicalScope","acceptanceCriteria","phase","phaseKey","metadata"],"values":{"priority":"P1","summary":"Keep CLI/cache overview on failed service promote and provide a feature-flag/config toggle to disable or revert service-primary promote.","description":"Plan WBS row: WBS-6 (6) — Safe fallback and rollback for service promote after first paint\n\nApproach:\nWhen post-paint promote to the dashboard service fails or returns worse data, keep the already-usable CLI/cache overview (fallback) and allow disable/revert of the promote path so operators are not stuck on a broken service-primary view. Document the activation toggle for service-primary promote.\n\nGoal mapping:\n- Quiet promote to service-primary without regressing an already-usable overview\n\nTechnical scope:\n- extensions/cursor-workflow-cannon/src/views/dashboard\n- service promote fallback path\n- feature flag or config toggle to disable service-primary promote\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- Failed or unhealthy service promote falls back to the already-usable CLI/cache overview without clearing it\n- Operators can disable or revert service-primary promote via feature flag or config toggle and remain on the cold-path overview\n- Deterministic test covers promote failure fallback and rollback/disable behavior\n\nVerification:\n- Unit test for promote failure fallback retaining CLI/cache overview\n- Unit test for disable/revert toggle keeping cold-path overview active\n\nDone means:\nPromote failure falls back to CLI/cache overview; disable/revert toggle works; both tested (completes R-3 mitigation).\n\nRisk notes:\nR-3: Fallback/disable is the safety net when quiet promote fails or regresses overview.","approach":"Keep CLI/cache overview on failed service promote and provide a feature-flag/config toggle to disable or revert service-primary promote.","dependsOn":["T100845","T100846"],"technicalScope":["extensions/cursor-workflow-cannon/src/views/dashboard","service promote fallback path","feature flag or config toggle to disable service-primary promote"],"acceptanceCriteria":["Failed or unhealthy service promote falls back to the already-usable CLI/cache overview without clearing it","Operators can disable or revert service-primary promote via feature flag or config toggle and remain on the cold-path overview","Deterministic test covers promote failure fallback and rollback/disable behavior"],"phase":"Phase 146","phaseKey":"146","metadata":{"planRef":"plan-artifact:60075304-3c0c-46c6-9c8f-468dd8ef6379","planningProvenance":{"planId":"60075304-3c0c-46c6-9c8f-468dd8ef6379","planVersion":15,"wbsId":"WBS-6","wbsPath":"6","planRef":"plan-artifact:60075304-3c0c-46c6-9c8f-468dd8ef6379","planningType":"change","sourceIdeaId":"I012","source":"persist-planning-execution-drafts"}}}},"workspace":{"phaseKey":"146"},"expectedTaskVersion":1}
